House Bill 656
By: Representatives Sainz of the 180th and Stephens of the 164th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 71 of Title 36 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 development impact fees, so as to authorize the assessment of development impact fees for
3 public facilities produced through agreements between developers and governmental entities;
4 to revise definitions; to extend the period of time a local government may encumber unspent
5 impact fees; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 71 of Title 36 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to development
9 impact fees, is amended by revising paragraphs (16) and (17) of Code Section 36-71-2,
10 relating to definitions, and by adding a new subparagraph to read as follows:
11 "(16) 'Proportionate share' means that portion of the cost of system improvements which
12 is reasonably related to the service demands and needs of the caused by a project within
13 the defined service area.
14 (17) 'Public facilities' means:
15 (A) Water supply production, treatment, and distribution facilities;
16 (B) Waste-water collection, treatment, and disposal facilities;
