26 paragraph that are the product of agreements between developers and governmental
27 entities."
28 SECTION 2.
29 Said chapter is further amended by revising paragraphs (1) and (2) of Code Section 36-71-9,
30 relating to refunds of development impact fees, as follows:
31 "(1) Upon the request of an owner of property on which a development impact fee has
32 been paid, a municipality or county shall refund the development impact fee if capacity
33 is available and service is denied or if the municipality or county, after collecting the fee
34 when service is not available, has failed to encumber the development impact fee or
35 commence construction within six ten years after the date that the fee was collected. In
36 determining whether development impact fees have been encumbered, development
37 impact fees shall be considered encumbered on a first-in, first-out (FIFO) basis;
38 (2) When the right to a refund exists due to a failure to encumber development impact
39 fees, the municipality or county shall provide written notice of entitlement to a refund to
40 the feepayor who paid the development impact fee at the address shown on the
41 application for development approval or to a successor in interest who has given notice
42 to the municipality or county of a transfer or assignment of the right or entitlement to a
